Key Match Events: The Padres won 5-3 against the Diamondbacks at Chase Field.
The Padres scored four runs in the first inning.
Corbin Carroll hit a leadoff homer for the Diamondbacks.
Eugenio Suárez hit an RBI single in the sixth inning.
Merrill Kelly struck out eight batters in 5 2/3 innings.
Pre-Game Insights: The Diamondbacks needed to win three games against the Padres to control their postseason fate.
Post-Match Reflections: D-backs manager Torey Lovullo expressed determination despite losing control of their postseason destiny.
Ketel Marte acknowledged the team's mistakes but remained hopeful.
Lovullo emphasized the team's readiness and determination to win the next game.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Diamondbacks are in a virtual three-way tie with the Mets and Braves for the National League's No. 2 Wild Card spot.
The D-backs lead baseball in runs scored.
